<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-26T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-26T14:00:00-05:00" n="618" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d618">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Fletcher</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-26T15:00:00-04:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 26, 1918, 3 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1405. See Consul Dawson’s August 21, 6 p.m. Bring substance thereof to
                            attention Mexican Government, and request it to take steps to extend
                            adequate protection for American life and property against bandits in
                            oil fields.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>